<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Fresno Climate</h2>
<p>For Fresno's hot-dry climate, high-efficiency air conditioning systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are recommended to handle the intense summer cooling demands. The most cost-effective options include 18-20 SEER central air systems paired with variable-speed air handlers, which provide consistent comfort while reducing energy consumption by up to 30%. Heat pumps are increasingly popular, offering efficient cooling in summer and supplemental heating during mild winters, though a backup heating source may be needed for the occasional cold snap below 35¬∞F. Due to Fresno's low humidity, evaporative coolers can be effective supplemental cooling for shoulder seasons, reducing overall HVAC runtime and energy costs. System sizing is critical ‚Äì oversized units cycle frequently and waste energy, while undersized systems struggle during peak summer temperatures, making proper load calculations essential for optimal performance.</p>

